cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL

The paper deals with the issue of miscalibration in machine learning models, which is a common problem in various subfields of computer science such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method, Neural Calibration, is a post-hoc calibration method that can be applied to any machine learning model, making it relevant to a wide range of applications in these subfields. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR, and cs.CL, in that order.
